🧊 Project Silica

What it is

Project Silica is Microsoft’s experimental storage system that writes data into glass using femtosecond lasers.

Key idea
	•	Data is stored as tiny structural changes inside the glass
	•	These changes are 3D + orientation + intensity
	•	That’s why they call it “5D storage”

Why it matters
	•	Durability: survives heat, water, EM pulses
	•	Longevity: thousands of years
	•	Read-only archive: like a permanent memory crystal

👉 Think of it as:

“Hard drive → but the bits are physically engraved into space itself.”

⸻

🧊 Voxels (Volumetric Pixels)

What they are

A voxel = a 3D pixel (volume element)

Instead of:
	•	2D image → pixels (x, y)

You get:
	•	3D space → voxels (x, y, z)

Used in:
	•	Games (e.g. Minecraft)
	•	Medical scans (CT/MRI)
	•	Physics simulations
	•	3D modeling

👉 Think of it as:

“Reality or data chopped into little cubes you can write values into.”

⸻

🔗 Where They Connect (This is the interesting part)

Project Silica is basically writing data into voxels inside glass.

But not just simple voxels…

It’s more like:

Each “voxel” contains:
	•	Position (x, y, z)
	•	Orientation (angle)
	•	Strength (intensity)

So each point = multi-dimensional voxel

👉 A better term:

“Hyper-voxel” or “5D voxel”

